                text: "Dolphins are some of the smartest animals on Earth. They live in oceans all around the world. Dolphins are mammals, just like humans. This means they breathe air and feed milk to their babies. A baby dolphin is called a calf. Dolphins live in groups called pods. They talk to each other using clicks and whistles. Each dolphin has its own special whistle, like a name. Dolphins use echolocation to find food. They make sounds that bounce off objects and come back to them. This helps them see in dark or murky water. Dolphins love to play. They jump out of the water, ride waves, and play with seaweed. They have been known to help humans too. There are stories of dolphins saving swimmers from sharks. Dolphins sleep with one eye open. Half of their brain stays awake to watch for danger and remember to breathe. Scientists study dolphins to learn more about how they think and communicate. These amazing animals still have many secrets to discover.",
