                id: 109,
                title: "The Coding Club Mystery (J)",
                text: "When someone started sabotaging the coding club's projects, eighth-grader Amara knew she had to investigate. The club had been working for months on an app to help students find study partners. But someone kept deleting their code and leaving taunting messages. The principal wanted to shut down the computer lab until the culprit was found. Amara refused to let that happen. She started by analyzing the timestamps of when the sabotage occurred. The attacks always happened after school on Tuesdays and Thursdays. Next, she checked the login records. The school's system tracked who accessed the computers and when. Someone had been using the account of a student named Derek, but Derek had soccer practice during those times. Amara realized someone must have stolen his password. She set a trap by creating a fake project file with hidden tracking code. The next time someone deleted it, her code would record information about the attacker. Two days later, her trap worked. The saboteur turned out to be a student who had been rejected from the coding club last year. He had been angry and wanted revenge. Instead of just reporting him, Amara talked to him. She learned he felt embarrassed about not getting in and never got help to improve his skills. Amara convinced the club advisor to give him another chance with a mentor. The former saboteur eventually became one of the club's most dedicated members. He helped finish the study partner app, which won a district technology award. Amara learned that solving problems sometimes means understanding the person behind them. Her detective skills were good, but her compassion made the real difference.",
