                text: "The Martinez family thought it was the end of the world when their wifi stopped working on a Saturday morning. Thirteen-year-old twins Elena and Miguel immediately started complaining. No streaming, no gaming, no video calls with friends. Their parents decided not to rush to fix it. Instead, they declared it a technology-free day, much to the twins' horror. Without screens to stare at, Elena and Miguel were forced to find other entertainment. Elena discovered a dusty box of art supplies in the closet. She had forgotten how much she used to love drawing. Miguel found an old basketball in the garage and convinced his dad to play one-on-one. Their mom suggested they cook lunch together instead of ordering delivery. Making homemade pizza from scratch turned into a hilarious flour fight. The kitchen was a mess, but everyone was laughing. After lunch, the family played board games they had not touched in years. Competitive Monopoly led to dramatic accusations of cheating. They talked and joked more in one afternoon than they had in weeks. As the sun set, they went for a walk around the neighborhood. They met neighbors they had never spoken to before. An elderly man shared stories about what the area looked like fifty years ago. When the wifi came back on Sunday morning, something had changed. The twins did not immediately grab their devices. They asked if they could make breakfast together first. Their parents smiled at each other. Sometimes losing something helps you find what you were missing all along.",
