                title: "Standing Up to Bullying (J)",
                text: "Eighth-grader Destiny had always been quiet and kept to herself. She preferred reading books to socializing. But when she witnessed a group of students bullying a new kid named Ahmed in the cafeteria, something inside her snapped. Ahmed had recently arrived from another country. His English was still developing, and some students mocked how he spoke. They knocked his lunch tray out of his hands and laughed as his food scattered across the floor. Destiny felt her heart pounding as she stood up. Her hands were shaking, but her voice was steady when she told them to stop. The bullies were surprised that quiet Destiny was challenging them. One of them asked why she cared. \"Because this is wrong,\" she said simply. \"Would you want someone treating you like that in a new country where you knew no one?\" Other students started watching. A few stood up and joined Destiny. The bullies, now outnumbered, backed off with embarrassed looks. After that day, Destiny and Ahmed became friends. She helped him with English while he taught her words in Arabic. Their friendship showed other students that differences should be celebrated, not mocked. The principal heard about what happened and invited Destiny to help create a new anti-bullying program. She learned that courage is not the absence of fear but taking action despite being afraid. One person standing up can inspire others to do the same. By the end of the year, the school culture had transformed. Students were more welcoming to newcomers, and incidents of bullying decreased significantly.",
